[h3 id=Stage-by-stagecomments: 
	[b 
		"Stage-by-stage comments:
	]b
	$LF
]h3
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 1 - Escape in a Forest
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" 1+2 trick is used twice. It's actually faster than dodging/taking damage, respectively.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Picks 100 more nippo. Increasing nippo is required to save time later.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Optimized 1 frame throwing a shuriken on boss, while the other frames is 'undetectable' lag reduction.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" When you finishes each chapter, you gain 200 nippo.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 2 - Pursuit in Tokyo
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Instead to take damage after the first ladder, getting a lower position is actually faster, and also skips a enemy.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" First shortcut of this TAS saves almost 2 seconds. Requires cancel climbing trick (1 frame before you exit the wall, press Up+1) + a good manipulation of 2 enemies, in order to perform this shortcut.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Better optimization on the rest of the stage, including an another shortcut.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" No improvements on the boss.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 3 - Samurai in Kendo
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Better optimization.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" This is the only stage that shows the large shuriken, which was used only once, since costs 10 nippo.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" I saved 4 frames on the first hit at the boss by using sword while on air.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 4 - Rescue Geisha
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Finally get 999 nippo! That's because game not deduct nippo after exceding 999. So, with this bug, I skip the spread shuriken and use homing fireballs (since homing fireballs costs 40 nippo, unlike the spread shuriken, that costs 20 nippo), saving some time.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" 3 new shortcuts. It's much faster than walljumping.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Avoiding the use of 1+2 during the third part of this stage.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Better optimization on the boss.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 5 - Enemy Turf
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" With homing fireballs, I don't need to press 1+2 to defeat that fish before getting the firewheel.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" When you turnaround during the fallings, normally you lose speed on the ice floors, but if you press the subweapon or attack animation before you reaches, you recover normal speed.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" On the boss, it's possible to hit when he's hidden. Also, on the start of the battle, I used 1+2 twice, in order to defeat without losing time.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 6 - Raid
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" Only better optimization during the stage.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" With the heavy use of firewhell and cancel climbing, I could hit the boss 4 times on each cycle instead of 2 times, saving energy to abuse of button 1+2 trick. So, I reduced 2.5 cycles, that results on a biggest improvement of this run.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 7 - Overcome
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" More better optimization, including 3 new shortcuts.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" While waiting for platform spawns, I picks homing missle again, saving time on the first hit. Also, I improved the boss without losing time.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[p 
	[b 
		"Chapter 8 - A Decisive Battle
	]b
	$LF
]p
[ul 
	[li 
		" With homing fireballs, I hit both bosses much earlier.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
[ul 
	[li 
		" Input ends earlier loading the homing fireballs instead of sword directly on the second boss.
		$LF
	]li
]ul
